<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="388" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1017,1043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name comes from the Latin and refers to the dorsal fin-like process of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[244,328,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,557,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1897]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–42. Amblyscarta pinna sp. nov., male. 35. Body, dorsal view. 36. Body, lateral view. 37. Face, frontal view. 38. Genital capsule, lateral view. 39. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 40. Connective and style, dorsal view. 41. Aedeagus, lateral view. 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3577121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3577121/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). It is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="388" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1089,1115]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species can be promptly recognized by the peculiar fin-like process of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 35–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,557,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1897]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–42. Amblyscarta pinna sp. nov., male. 35. Body, dorsal view. 36. Body, lateral view. 37. Face, frontal view. 38. Genital capsule, lateral view. 39. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 40. Connective and style, dorsal view. 41. Aedeagus, lateral view. 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3577121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3577121/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
), which is unique within the genus. As in the case of the two previous new taxa, the color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1428,1124,1152]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,557,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1897]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–42. Amblyscarta pinna sp. nov., male. 35. Body, dorsal view. 36. Body, lateral view. 37. Face, frontal view. 38. Genital capsule, lateral view. 39. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 40. Connective and style, dorsal view. 41. Aedeagus, lateral view. 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3577121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3577121/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">Figs 35, 36</figureCitation>
) will readily distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli, 2019" authorityName="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2019" box="[414,508,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Amblyscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinna" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[414,508,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">A. pinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[514,603,1161,1187]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,603,1161,1187]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from those poorly known species that were not included in 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, D. A." box="[1263,1436,1161,1187]" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 1135" refId="ref7297" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, i-vi + 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young’s (1977)</bibRefCitation>
key (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jacobi" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[208,343,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Amblyscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervicula">
<emphasis box="[208,343,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">A. cervicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fowler" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[357,458,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Amblyscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignea">
<emphasis box="[357,458,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">A. lignea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[472,596,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tettigonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[472,596,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">A. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[658,782,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Amblyscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaumi">
<emphasis box="[658,782,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="388">A. schaumi</emphasis>
